tldr: The user requested to implement a database for questionnaire responses, a
  client dashboard, and necessary middleware for a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application. The plan involved updating demographics, creating a Prisma model,
  building API routes, implementing simple password authentication, and
  developing an admin dashboard with CSV export, all of which were successfully
  implemented.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application by integrating a database for response storage and developing an
  admin dashboard for client access. After evaluating the existing codebase, it
  was determined that a database model for questionnaire responses, API routes
  for data handling, an authentication system, and the dashboard itself were
  missing. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for the
  database, implementing a simple password-based authentication via environment
  variables and HTTP-only cookies, and combining demographic data fields to meet
  both SOW and existing form requirements. The implementation involved updating
  data structures, creating new API endpoints for saving, retrieving, and
  exporting responses as CSV, and building a client-side admin dashboard with
  login and data viewing functionalities. All specified components were
  successfully integrated, providing a complete solution for data management and
  client access.
